**Police and Thief Game Description in detail with code explanation**

**Grid Class**

1- Created private fields of width, height, and 2D grid

       private int width; //col  
        private int height; //rows  
        private char\[,\] grid;

Making them private ensures that they cannot be accessed or changed directly from outside of class Grid, following the principle of encapsulation in OOP, it helps to protect the internal state of the object from unrequired interference. This also gives control over the fields like how they could be accessed by the other methods in the grid’s state

2- Created the parameterized constructor method 

 public Grid(int width, int height)  
 {  
     this.width \= width;   
     this.height \= height;  
     grid \= new char\[width, height\];  
     CreateGrid();   
 }

* This constructor has only 2 parameters width and height because they will determine the size of the grid, the other field 2D grid is not taken as a parameter because it is dependent on these width and height dimensions and is initialized based on them.  
* Here this keyword refers to the current instance of a class, it distinguishes between the class’s fields and parameters passed in constructors if they have the same names. Using (this. width) and (this. height) refers to private fields of the class not the parameters of the constructors.The width and height after (=) refer to the value passed as an argument to the constructor's parameter.  
* The 2D array is created in the constructor as it stores characters that represent different elements in the grid like empty spaces, boundaries, objects, etc. When the Grid object of class Grid is created in the program class this constructor initializes the 2D array with the given dimensions for height and width.  
* The CreateGrid() method is called in the constructor to set its initial state and the Grid object is created and it fills it will empty spaces and sets the boundaries. Using this method after creating a 2D array object in the constructor ensures that the grid is ready for use.

3- Creating a Method for Creating Grid CreateGrid()

**//creating a grid with empty spaces**  
public void CreateGrid()  
 {  
     for(int row \= 0; row \< height; row++)  
     {  
         for(int col \= 0; col \< width; col++)  
         {  
             grid\[row, col\] \= ' ';  
         }  
     }

* Using for nested loop created a grid with rows \= height and col \= width and created empty spaces in the grid

     **//Creating boundaries of the grid using for loop**  
     for(int col \= 0;col \< width; col++)   
     {  
         grid\[0,col\]= '\*'; **/**/upper boundary  
         grid\[height \- 1, col\]= '\*'; //lower boundary, height \- 1 refers to the last row (index 24\)  
     }   

     for(int row \= 0; row \< height; row++)  
     {  
         grid\[row,0\] \= '\*'; //left boundary  
         grid\[row, width \- 1\] \= '\*'; //right boundary, width \- 1 refers to the last col (index 99\)

     }

* Created upper and lower boundaries using for loop which sets the boundaries for the using \* covering the top, bottom, left, and right edges. Expressions height \- 1 \= 24 is for the last index of rows and width \- 1 \= 99 is for the last index of columns.

                                     
 0 ➡️                            Cols \= width \= 100   (upper boundary)   grid\[0,co\]                                                                col

|                                                                                                                                                    ⬆️ Rows \= height \= 25                                                                                                                                 width \- 1 \= 99 Left boundary: grid\[row,0\]                                                                                     Right boundary:grid\[row,width-1\] |
| :---- |

Height \- 1 \= 24                        grid\[height- 1, col\]                                                                                                                                     0  
(start of bottom boundary)

* The first loop iterates over columns (width) to set the top and bottom boundaries  
  While the second loop iterates over rows(height) to set the left and right boundaries.

5- Created a method DisplayGrid()  for diaplying the grid 

 public void DisplayGrid()  
 {  
     for (int row \= 0; row \< height; row++)  
     {  
         for (int col \= 0; col \< width; col++)  
         {  
             //Decalring a variable to hold character value and intialized with the value at the current position on grid  
             char character \= grid\[row, col\];  
             if (character \== 'P')  
             {  
                 Console.ForegroundColor \= ConsoleColor.Green;  
             }  
             if (character \== 'T')  
             {  
                 Console.ForegroundColor \= ConsoleColor.Red;  
             }  
             if (character \== 'C')  
             {  
                 Console.ForegroundColor \= ConsoleColor.Yellow;  
    }  
             else  
             {  
                 Console.ForegroundColor \= ConsoleColor.White;   
             }  
             Console.Write(character);  
         }  
         Console.WriteLine();  
     }  
     Console.ResetColor(); //Reset color after drawing the grid

Used DisplayGrid() method to display the grid using for loop in the method and that for loop declared variable character with datatype char and initialized it with grid array grid\[row, col\] after that used if statement with character as a condition for representation different types of persons on grid-like to represent them with different characters and colors on the grid. After that used Console. Write a method to write those characters on the grid and then use the console. writeline to move them to a new line and then reset the colors with the console. resetcolor method. In this way, the grid is displayed with different types of persons with their different character representations and colors.

Here `lastInteractionMessage` was passed to the `Interaction` method with the `ref` keyword, any change made inside the method would update the original variable.The "ref string" in this context is used to allow the method to manipulate the original string (`lastInteractionMessage`) directly. It acts as a reference to the original data, enabling efficient memory usage and the ability to change the original value.

 class Police: Persons //Police  
 {

Created a constructor for police subclass with its common parameters.

   //Override PersonRepresentation()  
   public override char PersonRepresentation \=\> 'P';  
Override the PersonRepersenetation method to represent police with character P.

    //Override Interaction method  
    public override void Interaction(Persons otherPerson, ref string lastInteractionMessage)  
    {  
          
        if (otherPerson is Thief thief && thief.StolenItems.Count \> 0\)  
        {  
            lastInteractionMessage \= $"Police caught Thief and confiscated stolen items: {string.Join(", ",thief.StolenItems)} ";  
            thief.StolenItems.Clear();  
        }  
        else if ( otherPerson is Citizen)  
        {  
            lastInteractionMessage \= $"Police met Citzien.No action taken";   
        }  
    }  
}  
Override the Interaction method and used if statement to show what will happen if the interaction will be between Police and the other person will be thief  and thief has some stolen items whose count is greater than 0  then what will be printed on console and if other person is citizen then what will be printed.

 class Thief: Persons //Thief  
 {  
 //Unique property of class Thief  
    public List\<string\> StolenItems {  get; set; }   
Created a unique property of thief subclass which is stolen items.  
//constructor  
public Thief (int xCoordinate, int yCoordinate) : base (xCoordinate, yCoordinate)   
{  
 //Initialized the unique property as empty at the start of the game  
 StolenItems \= new List\<string\>();  
}  
Created the constructor with common and unique properties of the thief class and initialized the unique property stolen items to empty because at the start of the game thief would have 0 stolen items.

 //Override PersonRepresentation()  
public override char PersonRepresentation \=\> 'T';  
Override the PersonRepersenetation method to represent police with character T.

 //Override Interaction method  
 public override void Interaction(Persons otherPerson, ref string lastInteractionMessage)  
 {  
     if (otherPerson is Citizen citizen && citizen.Inventory.Count \> 0\)  
     {  
         //creating a variable itemIndex and intialized to random  
         int itemIndex \= random.Next(citizen.Inventory.Count);  
         string stolenItem \= citizen.Inventory\[itemIndex\];  
         //Remove an item from citizen inventory according to index of item   
         citizen.Inventory.RemoveAt(itemIndex);  
         //Add that item to stolen items  
         StolenItems.Add(stolenItem);  
         //Print the last interaction on console  
         lastInteractionMessage \= $"Thief met Citizen";  
         lastInteractionMessage \= $"Thief stole {stolenItem} from a citizen.";  
     }

     else if (otherPerson is Police)  
     {  
         if (StolenItems.Count \> 0\)  
         {  
             lastInteractionMessage \= $"Police met Thief and confiscated stolen items: {string.Join(", ", StolenItems)}";  
             StolenItems.Clear();  
         }  
     }       
 }

Override the interaction method  using if else statement to show the interactions,if the other person is citizen then the following conditions will be implied : declared a variable (itemIndex) and used Random.Next method to take the items randomly from citizens inventory. Then made a variable of stolen items which shows the citizen inventory with items index. After that removed an item from citizens inventory by using (RemoveAt)  abd then added that stolen item to in stolen item property.And if the other person is police then if stolen items count is greater than 0  then the police wull take all things from thief and the stolen items property will again be empty.

 }
